    "body": "### Problem\n\nafter update to neovim-nightly, floating statusline break my plugins.\n\n<img width=\"2880\" height=\"1800\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c86bf0cc-d1b5-45e5-8037-8d57357e16ac\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\njust install [picker.nvim](https://github.com/wsdjeg/picker.nvim)\n\nopen picker files with `:Picker files`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nthe statusline should not be enabled in floating windows.\n\nthere should be an option to enable floating statsuline, by default it should be diabled by default.\n\n`laststatus=4` enable floating statusline?\n\nor  `nvim_open_win`  ops with `statusline = true`, false by default.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwin 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nno\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop install neovim-nightly",
